Use Disk Cleanup to Delete Old Updates From the SxS Folder
Open the Disk Cleanup tool. ... 
Click the "Cleanup system files" button. 
Check the box next to "Windows Update Cleanup." 
Click OK. 
Launch the command prompt with admin priviledges. ... 
Enter the command: Dism.exe /online /Cleanup-Image /StartComponentCleanup. 
Delete Software Distribution folder. ... Now browse to the C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution folder and delete all the files and folders inside. You may press Ctrl+A to Select All and then click on Delete. If the files are in use, and you are unable to delete some files, restart your device.Feb 25, 2016
Rename or delete Software Distribution folder in Windows 10/8/7

